    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nNeovim implements the `textDocument/publishDiagnostic` specification\r\nfor the diagnostics feature. Where the server notifies the client of this event.\r\n\r\n[LSP 3.17 implemented the `textDocument/pullDiagnostic` specification](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#textDocument_pullDiagnostics),\r\nthat expects the client to send `textDocument/diagnostic` requests to the server\r\nwhen the client wants diagnostics updates.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSupport `textDocument/diagnostic feature out of the box.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Extra information:\r\n\r\n* [Related nvim-lspconfig PR](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/2498) that implements a workaround for `ruby-lsp` to send `textDocument/diagnostic` requests to the Server, and treat the response like it was for a `textDocument/publishDiagnostic` event.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
